# Project Rules: __PROJECT_NAME__

> Updated on: __DATE__

These rules turn document-driven development from a suggestion into the default working mode.

## Rule Guide

- `docs/rules/clarification-rules.md`: requirement clarification and confirmation rules
- `docs/rules/coding-standards.md`: coding rules and boundaries
- `docs/rules/bug-fix-rules.md`: root-cause bug fixing and regression rules
- `docs/rules/testing-standards.md`: testing and regression expectations
- `docs/rules/doc-sync-rules.md`: documentation and code sync rules
- `docs/rules/change-management-rules.md`: change-tracking rules for requirements, bug fixes, and releases
- `docs/rules/issue-management-rules.md`: issue tracking and archive rules
- `docs/rules/definition-of-done.md`: completion checklist
- `docs/rules/document-routing-rules.md`: semantic-to-path routing rules

## How to use this directory

1. Read this directory before implementation starts
2. When a trade-off appears, check whether a default rule already exists here
3. As the project evolves, add new rules here instead of leaving them in chat or PR comments only
